      "DM CONSULTANTS is associated with the IRCC that provide consultation and guidance information in relation to the immigration policies in Canada. However, DM CONSULTANTS reserves the right to update or change the contract with any of these IRCC Agents. In place of such circumstance, such will be done with the interest of our Client as a priority. DM CONSULTANTS is not responsible for the loss of documents in transit as this is the responsibility of the courier company. DM CONSULTANTS recommends that all correspondence be sent by registered mail or with a reputable international courier and the Client should notify DM CONSULTANTS before dispatching any documentation.",
      "In case of refiling, the Client shall pay additional Fees if the contract is outside the validity, as per the policy of DM CONSULTANTS.",
