      "Definitions and Interpretation",
      "\"DM Consultants\" shall mean and include all branches, subsidiaries, and affiliates of DM, including, but not limited to, its operations in the Middle East and in the jurisdictions of India, the United Arab Emirates (UAE), Oman, Kuwait, Qatar, and the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. DM is the licensed immigration agent with its head office in Dubai, United Arab Emirates.",
      "\"Immigration consultant\" means an individual/an entity who provides nonlegal assistance or advice on an immigration matter including:(a) completing a document provided by a federal or state agency, but not advising a person as to the person's answers on the document (b) translating a person's answer to a question posed in a document provided by a federal or state agency; (c) securing for a person supporting documents, that may be necessary to complete a document provided by a federal or state agency; (d) submitting a completed document on a person's behalf and at the person's request to the Authorities; or (e) for valuable consideration, referring a person to a person who could undertake legal representation activities in an immigration matter.",
      "\"Services\" Services available under this Contract are limited to those services specifically refers to the immigration consultancy services more detailed in Annexure A.",
      "\"Confidential Information\" refers to all non-public information provided by one party to the other for the purpose of fulfilling this Agreement.",
